### Authentication Endpoints (BFF Pattern)
### Google OAuth with HTTP-only cookie session

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@apiBaseUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

###
# 1. Initiate Google OAuth Login
# User is redirected to Google consent screen
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/google
# Returns: 302 Redirect to Google OAuth

###
# 2. OAuth Callback (handled by API, not called directly)
# After Google authentication, Google redirects to this endpoint
# GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/google/callback?code={authorization_code}&state={csrf_token}
# Returns: 302 Redirect to /dashboard with Set-Cookie header (HTTP-only)

###
# 3. Check Authentication Status
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: .AspNetCore.Identity.Application={session_cookie}
# Returns: 200 OK
# {
#   "userId": "google-oauth2|123456789",
#   "email": "user@gmail.com",
#   "isAuthenticated": true
# }

###
# 4. Sign Out
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/signout
Cookie: .AspNetCore.Identity.Application={session_cookie}
# Returns: 200 OK (clears cookie)

###
# 5. Health Check (includes auth status)
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/health
# Returns: 200 OK
# {
#   "status": "Healthy",
#   "checks": {
#     "tableStorage": "Healthy",
#     "authentication": "Healthy"
#   }
# }
